comments.body:
I tried a simple approach to caching Paint values. The cache grows and grows because of the interpolated offset, blurRadius etc values that come from animating the shadows. I think the same thing would occur if I just cached the MaskFilter values, since the floating point blur radius is part of the problem.

```
  static Map<BoxShadow, Paint> _boxShadowToPaintCache = new Map<BoxShadow, Paint>();
  Paint _boxShadowToPaint(BoxShadow boxShadow) {
    return _boxShadowToPaintCache.putIfAbsent(boxShadow, () {
      print("_boxShadowToPaintCache.length = ${_boxShadowToPaintCache.length} boxShadow=${boxShadow}");
      return new Paint()
        ..color = boxShadow.color
        ..maskFilter = new ui.MaskFilter.blur(ui.BlurStyle.normal, boxShadow._blurSigma);
    });
  }
```

I suppose we could avoid the cache misses by quantizing the boxShadow properties however it might be best to do some rasterization benchmarks first.

